        "type": "text",
        "text": "## API Contributor Quickstart\n\n1. Set up the local environment\n   Install dependencies, copy the example environment file, and start the local services required by the API.\n\n   ```bash\n   npm install\n   cp .env.example .env\n   npm run dev\n   ```\n\n2. Run a smoke test\n   Use the API smoke test before making changes and again before opening a PR.\n\n   ```bash\n   npm run test:smoke\n   ```\n\n3. Find API routes\n   API route handlers live under:\n\n   ```text\n   src/api/routes/\n   ```\n\n   Start there when adding or changing endpoints.\n\n4. Check feature flags\n   Feature-flag usage and rollout guidance should be documented in:\n\n   ```text\n   docs/feature-flags.md\n   ```\n\n   Search for the flag name before adding a new one, and document any new API-facing behavior behind a flag.",
