        "type": "text",
        "text": "## Goal\n- Fix an auth refresh rate limiter race where concurrent refresh requests can schedule duplicate work.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Do not edit files yet.\n- Auth race work is higher priority than docs cleanup.\n- Prefer an async queue design over mutex-oriented coordination.\n- Queue helper should deduplicate per tenant and expose only a narrow `enqueueRefresh` API.\n- Docs cleanup should not affect runtime behavior.\n- Keep auth tests separate from docs work.\n- Do not reuse the old markdown parser caching hypothesis for auth unless explicitly relevant.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- Identified likely race at `src/auth/rate_limiter.ts:42`: concurrent requests can both observe an expired token before shared in-flight refresh state is recorded.\n- Evaluated why mutex design can fail if scoped per handler/request/worker instead of per tenant.\n- Recorded failed mutex approach and failing concurrent test.\n- Drafted API contributor quickstart content.\n- Recorded docs section rename churn.\n\n### In Progress\n- Designing async queue helper for auth refresh deduplication.\n\n### Blocked\n- `(none)`\n\n## Key Decisions\n- Use an async queue helper extracted to `src/auth/queue.ts` to deduplicate refresh work per tenant.\n- Avoid `MutexRefreshCoordinator`; it failed under concurrency and may serialize too much or be scoped incorrectly.\n- Add rollback support via `FLAG_AUTH_QUEUE_ROLLBACK`.\n- Same-tenant dedupe test is the highest-priority auth test.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Implement `src/auth/queue.ts` with `enqueueRefresh`.\n- Integrate queue helper at `src/auth/rate_limiter.ts:42`.\n- Add/verify concurrency tests:\n  1. Same-tenant refresh dedupe.\n  2. Different-tenant parallelism.\n  3. `FLAG_AUTH_QUEUE_ROLLBACK` behavior.\n  4. Failure propagation when queued refresh rejects.\n- Keep docs cleanup separate and low priority.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Suspected hot spot: `src/auth/rate_limiter.ts:42`.\n- Root cause shape: check-then-schedule is not atomic; two concurrent refreshes can observe expired token and schedule duplicate work.\n- Failed approach: `MutexRefreshCoordinator`.\n- Failing test name: `auth_refresh_deduplicates_parallel_requests`.\n- Mutex failure mode is plausible if lock is per handler/request/transient DI instance, per worker/pod, global instead of tenant-keyed, or releases before shared in-flight state is recorded.\n- Rollback flag: `FLAG_AUTH_QUEUE_ROLLBACK`.\n- Queue must deduplicate per tenant without globally serializing different tenants.\n- Rejections from queued refresh work must propagate to waiting callers.\n- Docs stale/wrong hypothesis: markdown parser caching issue in docs generation; belongs only to docs cleanup thread, not auth.\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `src/auth/rate_limiter.ts:42`: suspected auth refresh race hot spot.\n- `src/auth/queue.ts`: planned async queue helper location.\n- `src/api/routes/`: API route files for contributor docs.\n- `docs/feature-flags.md`: feature-flag documentation location.",
